response: "{ \"title\": \"Medium: Fibonacci Sequence\", \"description\": \"The Fibonacci sequence is a series of numbers in which each number (Fibonacci number) is the sum of the two preceding ones, usually starting with 0 and 1. Write a function `fibonacci` that returns the nth term of the Fibonacci sequence.\\n\\n#### Function Signature\\n```python\\ndef fibonacci(n: int) -> int:\\n```\\n\\n#### Input\\n- `n` (int): The position in the Fibonacci sequence to return. It must be a non-negative integer.\\n\\n#### Output\\n- Returns the nth term of the Fibonacci sequence.\\n\", \"code\": \"def fibonacci(n: int) -> int:\\n    if n == 0:\\n        return 0\\n    elif n == 1:\\n        return 1\\n    else:\\n        a, b = 0, 1\\n        for _ in range(2, n + 1):\\n            a, b = b, a + b\\n        return b\\n\", \"tests\": [\"assert fibonacci(0) == 0\", \"assert fibonacci(1) == 1\", \"assert fibonacci(6) == 8\", \"assert fibonacci(10) == 55\"] }"
